The paper discusses the use of the Burrows-Wheeler transform (BWT) for compression and indexing of text data, specifically genomic sequence data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DB (Databases). However, given the focus on compression and indexing, cs.DS and cs.CE are the most likely categories. The use of the BWT also suggests a potential connection to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG), while the focus on genomic sequence data suggests a potential connection to databases (cs.DB).
